>And while were at it any pics etc of where the thermostat etc is located and
>what to not see if its missing !
>All this thermostat talk has got me worried :)

It's located above the air deflection plate that protects the push rod tubes for cylinders #1/#2. There a pulley that connects the thermostat to the spring on the flap next to the oil breather chimney.

Here's an exploded view of the thermostat:

